## **2(i) Abstract (‚â§ 300 words)**

**Exam-Perfect Abstract (you can write this directly):**

Sleep quality plays a crucial role in maintaining physical health, mental well-being, and cognitive performance. Traditional sleep assessment techniques such as polysomnography (PSG), although accurate, are expensive, intrusive, and unsuitable for continuous home monitoring. This has motivated the development of automated and non-intrusive sleep analysis systems using artificial intelligence.

This project proposes an AI-based framework for sleep quality analysis using multimodal physiological and lifestyle data. The dataset includes parameters such as sleep duration, heart rate, oxygen saturation (SpO‚ÇÇ), body movement, stress levels, and demographic factors. Feature extraction is performed to capture meaningful sleep-related characteristics, and a Random Forest classification model is employed to categorize sleep quality into good, average, and poor.

Random Forest is chosen due to its ability to handle heterogeneous data, model non-linear relationships, and provide robustness against noisy physiological signals. Feature importance analysis further enhances model interpretability by identifying key factors influencing sleep quality. Experimental results demonstrate improved classification accuracy compared to traditional machine learning models.

The proposed system enables scalable, interpretable, and non-intrusive sleep quality assessment, making it suitable for long-term home-based monitoring and early detection of sleep-related health issues.

