## **2(iv) Algorithm Explanation ‚Äì Random Forest**

**Answer:**

Random Forest is an ensemble learning algorithm that consists of multiple decision trees. Each decision tree is trained using a random subset of the dataset and a random selection of features. This randomness ensures diversity among the trees.

When a new sleep data sample is provided, it is passed through all decision trees. Each tree independently predicts the sleep quality class. The final classification result is obtained using majority voting among all trees. This ensemble approach reduces overfitting and improves generalization performance.

Random Forest is well suited for sleep quality analysis because physiological data is multimodal, noisy, and non-linear. The algorithm can effectively handle mixed data types and provides feature importance scores, which help identify key physiological factors affecting sleep quality.

